    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/821: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macedo Soares</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-20">February 20,
                            1936</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to communicate to Your Excellency that the President of the
                    Republic of the United States of Brazil confers, by <pb facs="0394" n="295"
                        xml:id="pg_295"/> the present telegram, full powers on the Ambassador of
                    Brazil at your capital, Mr. Oswaldo Aranha, to sign, as representative of the
                    Brazilian Government and of the Bank of Brazil (<hi rend="italic">Banco do
                        Brasil</hi>), with the National Foreign Trade Council an agreement for the
                    liquidation of the commercial debts between Brazil and the United States of
                    America which are overdue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">José Carlos de Macedo Soares</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
